Step 1. Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 3,376,304.04 and Total Owner's Equity = 16,143,922.03.  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = 3,376,304.04 / 16,143,922.03 ≈ 0.21  

Step 2. Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 143,922.03 and Total Revenue = 851,679.79.  
• Net Profit Margin = (143,922.03 / 851,679.79) x 100 ≈ 16.91%  

Step 3. Return on Assets (ROA)  
• Total Assets at period end = 19,520,226.07.  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) x 100 = (143,922.03 / 19,520,226.07) x 100 ≈ 0.74%  

Step 4. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Accounts Receivable went from an initial 0.00 to an ending 335,967.05. The average AR = (0 + 335,967.05)/2 = 167,983.525.  
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average AR = 851,679.79 / 167,983.525 ≈ 5.07  

Thus, the answer is:  
{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.21", 
    "Net Profit Margin": "16.91%", 
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "0.74%", 
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "5.07"
  }
}
